Bash

```json
{
  "language": "Bash",
  "description": "This script is a meteorological data processing workflow designed to extract and process various meteorological datasets, including ERA5, Daymet, ESPO-G6-R2, and more. It offers options for specifying the dataset, variables, time range, spatial extent, and ensemble members to process. The script utilizes GDAL for spatial extent extraction and supports parallel processing via SLURM job submission. It includes functions for date chunking, script execution, and dataset validation.",
  "software_requirements": [
    "bash",
    "getopt",
    "date",
    "module",
    "gdal",
    "ogrinfo",
    "gdalsrsinfo",
    "gdaltransform",
    "sbatch (if submitting jobs to SLURM)"
  ],
  "resource_requirements": [
    "SLURM (optional, for job submission)",
    "cache directory (for temporary data storage)",
    "scratch space (for temporary files)"
  ],
  "notes": [
    "The script assumes the user has access to the necessary meteorological datasets and associated scripts.",
    "The script utilizes a predefined list of datasets; additional datasets can be added by modifying the case statement.",
    "The script's behavior and output are dependent on the specific processing script used for each dataset."
  ]
}
```
